<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Solemnity" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Solemnity,</orth> 1) ceremony performed (especially the celebration of nuptials; cf. <emph>solemn</emph> in <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.187" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.392" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 392</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 88</bibl>); and hence, festivity: <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 224</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 139</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.376.139" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 376</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.555" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 555</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 59</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.369" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 369</bibl>.<lb />2) awful grandeur, stateliness, dignity: <cit><quote>my state, seldom but sumptuous, showed like a feast and won by rareness such s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 59</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>